What makes you say that? I mean, it's just  meat, one recipe has meat and sweet potatoes. So there isn't much in the way of ingredients. The website makes it seem like they're properly sourced/good quality, just wondering if anyone can vouch for that or has any positive/negative experiences.

[The company is Czech, been around since 1994](https://brit-petfood.com/en/company-profile) and seems established in some markets (EU, Asia).
